# Portfolio copy style

## No em dashes

Never use the em dash character (`—`, U+2014) in public-facing copy: UI strings, page content, project titles, experience descriptions, case studies, metadata, or README prose.

Use instead:
- Commas for appositives and name-to-role introductions
- Colons for titles with a subtitle segment (e.g. `Digital Ecosystem: Facultad de Comunicaciones y Filología, Universidad de Antioquia`)
- Periods to split sentences

Date ranges may use an en dash (`–`) between dates (e.g. `Nov 2021 – May 2026`).

When editing copy, grep for `\u2014` or `—` before finishing.
